      <rules>
        <rule id="4994-b3ff-7cfa-f545" name="Dwarf Troll Slayer" hidden="false">
          <description>May be Hired: Mercenaries and Witch Hunters may hire a Dwarf Troll Slayer.

Warbands that include Elves may hire Slayers, but must pay 20 gold crowns after each battle instead of 10 gold crowns.

Dwarfs won’t put up with weak pointy-eared folk unless they have to, or are adequately compensated for their sufferance.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule id="66b8-92c0-6052-ed52" name="Deathwish" hidden="false">
          <description>Troll Slayers seek an honourable death in combat.
They are completely immune to all psychology and will never need to test if they are fighting alone.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule id="b155-e858-4454-867f" name="Hard to Kill" hidden="false">
          <description>Troll Slayers are tough, resilient individuals who can only be taken out of action on a D6 roll of 6 instead of 5-6 when rolling on the Injury chart.
Treat a roll of 5 as stunned.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule id="8e62-755b-9c13-d5e2" name="Hard Head" hidden="false">
          <description>Troll Slayers ignore the special rules for maces, clubs etc.
They are not very easy individuals to knock out!</description>
        </rule>
      </rules>
      <infoLinks>
        <infoLink id="2f84-a1cf-25da-3f86" name="Dwarf max" hidden="false" targetId="20ca-82d5-4ea4-4152" type="profile"/>
      </infoLinks>
